                    },
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "B_ratio", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.5179697702828123},
                        {"variable": "S_f", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.1}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "depleted_litter_gates_burn",
                    "description": "M_litter = 0 < eps_fuel (1e-10) so the ifelse selects zero_dimless and the litter contribution to ground_burn_rate vanishes; trash and scrub still burn. V_A = 0 ⇒ B_ratio = 0.5. ground_burn_rate = (R_trash + R_scrub) * 0.5 = 0.0045 kg/(m^2*s); F_s = 0.97 * 1.7e7 * 0.0045 = 74205 W/m^2. Verifies the per-fuel eps_fuel gate stops consumption cleanly at depletion.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {"V_A": 0.0},
                    "initial_conditions": {
                        "M_litter": 0.0,
                        "M_trash": 0.5,
                        "M_scrub": 0.2,
                        "M_canopy": 1.2,
                        "Q_cumulative": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "ground_burn_rate", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0045},
                        {"variable": "total_burn_rate", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0045},
                        {"variable": "F_s", "time": 0.0, "expected": 74205.0}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "canopy_burning_when_Q_above_threshold",
                    "description": "Initialise Q_cumulative = 200000 J/m^2, above the 170000 J/m^2 canopy ignition threshold. canopy_burning flips to 1 at t = 0 and the canopy contributes to total_burn_rate. V_A = 0 ⇒ B_ratio = 0.5; total_burn_rate = ground (0.0245) + R_canopy*B_ratio*1*1 = 0.0245 + 0.01 = 0.0345 kg/(m^2*s); F_s = 0.97 * 1.7e7 * 0.0345 = 568905 W/m^2; F_l = 0.56*2.5e6*0.0345 + 0.03*1.7e7*0.0345 = 48300 + 17595 = 65895 W/m^2. Exercises the canopy_burning step function in Q_cumulative.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {"V_A": 0.0},
                    "initial_conditions": {
                        "M_litter": 2.0,
                        "M_trash": 0.5,
                        "M_scrub": 0.2,
                        "M_canopy": 1.2,
                        "Q_cumulative": 200000.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "canopy_burning", "time": 0.0, "expected": 1.0},
                        {"variable": "total_burn_rate", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0345},
                        {"variable": "F_s", "time": 0.0, "expected": 568905.0},
                        {"variable": "F_l", "time": 0.0, "expected": 65895.0}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "pre_ignition_linear_evolution_V_A_3",
                    "description": "Short-time linear evolution before the canopy-ignition switch. V_A = 3 gives constant B_ratio = sqrt(4/7), ground_burn_rate = 0.037040518... kg/(m^2*s), and dQ/dt = 0.97 * 1.7e7 * 0.037040518 = 610798.148 W/m^2 (J/m^2/s). The threshold (170000 J/m^2) is crossed at t ≈ 0.27832 s; sampling at t = 0.1 stays well inside the pre-ignition regime where every state evolves linearly: M_litter(0.1) = 2 - R_litter*B_ratio*0.1; M_trash(0.1) = 0.5 - R_trash*B_ratio*0.1; M_scrub(0.1) = 0.2 - R_scrub*B_ratio*0.1; Q_cumulative(0.1) = dQ/dt * 0.1 = 61079.81... J/m^2 (below threshold ⇒ canopy_burning = 0, M_canopy unchanged at 1.2).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {"V_A": 3.0},
                    "initial_conditions": {
                        "M_litter": 2.0,
                        "M_trash": 0.5,
                        "M_scrub": 0.2,
                        "M_canopy": 1.2,
                        "Q_cumulative": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 0.1},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "M_litter", "time": 0.1, "expected": 1.9969762841759817},
                        {"variable": "M_trash", "time": 0.1, "expected": 0.4996221855219977},
                        {"variable": "M_scrub", "time": 0.1, "expected": 0.1996977284175982},
                        {"variable": "M_canopy", "time": 0.1, "expected": 1.2},
                        {"variable": "Q_cumulative", "time": 0.1, "expected": 61079.81476723714},
                        {"variable": "canopy_burning", "time": 0.1, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": {"abs": 1.0e-15}}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "post_ignition_canopy_flag_V_A_3",
                    "description": "Run V_A = 3 m/s long enough to cross the canopy ignition threshold (t_ignite ≈ 0.27832 s) and confirm canopy_burning = 1 at t = 1.0 s. Q_cumulative growth is independent of canopy state (dQ/dt depends only on ground_burn_rate), and all ground fuels remain well-stocked over [0, 1] s ⇒ Q(1.0) = dQ/dt * 1.0 ≈ 610798.15 J/m^2 (well above the 170 kJ/m^2 threshold).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {"V_A": 3.0},
                    "initial_conditions": {
                        "M_litter": 2.0,
                        "M_trash": 0.5,
                        "M_scrub": 0.2,
                        "M_canopy": 1.2,
                        "Q_cumulative": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "canopy_burning", "time": 1.0, "expected": 1.0},
                        {"variable": "Q_cumulative", "time": 1.0, "expected": 610798.1476723714}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "ground_fuel_linear_decay_V_A_0",
                    "description": "Longer-horizon linear decay of the three ground fuels at V_A = 0 (B_ratio = 0.5, all fuels constant-rate). At t = 10 s: M_litter = 2.0 - 0.04*0.5*10 = 1.8; M_trash = 0.5 - 0.005*0.5*10 = 0.475; M_scrub = 0.2 - 0.004*0.5*10 = 0.18 (all comfortably above eps_fuel). Q_cumulative(10) = 404005 * 10 = 4040050 J/m^2 (dQ/dt is constant while ground fuels are all above eps_fuel). canopy_burning(10) = 1 (Q crossed threshold at t ≈ 0.42 s). M_canopy is NOT asserted at this sampling time — the ifelse switch around t ≈ 0.42 s creates small integrator-truncation error in the canopy state.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {"V_A": 0.0},
                    "initial_conditions": {
                        "M_litter": 2.0,
                        "M_trash": 0.5,
                        "M_scrub": 0.2,
                        "M_canopy": 1.2,
                        "Q_cumulative": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 10.0},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "M_litter", "time": 10.0, "expected": 1.8},
                        {"variable": "M_trash", "time": 10.0, "expected": 0.475},
                        {"variable": "M_scrub", "time": 10.0, "expected": 0.18},
                        {"variable": "Q_cumulative", "time": 10.0, "expected": 4040050.0},
                        {"variable": "canopy_burning", "time": 10.0, "expected": 1.0}
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "fir7cr_short_burn",
                    "description": "Short 30-second burn at V_A = 3 m/s (the FIR7CR experiment wind), starting from the moderately loaded dry-eucalyptus initial state used in the upstream docstring example (M_litter = 2.0, M_trash = 0.5, M_scrub = 0.2, M_canopy = 1.2 kg/m^2; Q_cumulative = 0). The canopy ignites automatically at t ≈ 0.28 s when Q_cumulative crosses 170 kJ/m^2; the full burn then drives F_s, F_l, and total_burn_rate at canopy-active levels through the end of the run. Reproduces the qualitative behaviour shown in Fig. 6 of Clark et al. (1996) over the first half-minute.",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "parameters": {
                        "V_A": 3.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 30.0},
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "ground_fuels_vs_time",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Ground-fuel masses (litter, trash, scrub) vs. time over the 30-second burn — illustrates the linear-decay regime and the ordering of depletion times set by the per-fuel R_i.",
                            "x": {"variable": "t", "label": "Time t (s)"},
                            "y": {"variable": "M_litter", "label": "Fuel mass (kg/m^2)"}
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "F_s_vs_time",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Surface sensible heat flux F_s vs. time. Step-up at t ≈ 0.28 s when the canopy ignites and joins the total burn rate.",
                            "x": {"variable": "t", "label": "Time t (s)"},
                            "y": {"variable": "F_s", "label": "Sensible heat flux F_s (W/m^2)"}
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "no_wind_baseline",
                    "description": "V_A = 0 m/s baseline: the McArthur spread rate S_f collapses to 0 (the wind-speed clamp wins) and B_ratio = 0.5 is the lower bound of the burn-rate ratio. All ground fuels still burn at half their nominal rate; the canopy ignites at t ≈ 0.42 s. Useful for isolating wind-independent terms when interpreting the wind-driven scenarios.",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "parameters": {
                        "V_A": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 30.0},
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "Q_cumulative_vs_time",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Cumulative ground heat flux Q_cumulative vs. time — linear ramp at dQ/dt = 0.97 * 1.7e7 * 0.0245 ≈ 404 kW/m^2 (constant while all ground fuels stay above eps_fuel). The 170 kJ/m^2 canopy-ignition threshold is crossed at t ≈ 0.42 s.",
                            "x": {"variable": "t", "label": "Time t (s)"},
                            "y": {"variable": "Q_cumulative", "label": "Cumulative ground heat flux (J/m^2)"}
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    }
